title: 5 Seconds of Summer Announce 'Sounds Live Feels Live' tour | Examiner.com
text:
Play 5 Seconds of Summer - "Hey Everybody [Official]" YouTube With the release of their sophomore album just a week away, 5 Seconds of Summer have decided to treat fans to a lot of good news to jumpstart their weekend. On Friday (Oct. 16), the Australian band not only released the music video for their latest single, "Hey Everybody," but they also unveiled the list of tour dates for the upcoming new year. Earlier this month, the four-piece had revealed they would be hitting the road in 2016 in support of their new record, Sounds Good Feels Good . At the time of the announcement, the only dates confirmed were those in the United Kingdom and Ireland.
Photo by Mike Coppola/Getty Images Now, the group has confirmed the complete itinerary for the North American leg of the tour. The "Sounds Live Feels Live Tour" will begin on July 1 at the Mohegan Sun Arena in Uncasville, CT. For two and a half months, the band will perform at a slew of US cities as well as two Canadian towns, playing shows for their dedicated fan base. The tour will then wrap up on Sept. 18 at the Cynthia Woods Mitchell Pavilion in Houston, TX. The complete list of tour dates can be seen below while the music video for "Hey Everybody" which features the boys stuck in dead-end jobs wondering what it would be like to be rich and not to worry about money can be seen above.

Before heading off on the "Sounds Live Feels Live Tour," the band will end 2015 as one of the many performers on this year's "iHeartRado Jingle Ball Tour." Dates for those shows can be seen here .
